✅ What is Drag and Drop?
- Drag and Drop is an UI action:
    - An element(source) is clicked and held
    - Moved to another element(target)
    - released

✅ How to Perform in Selenium?
- We use
    - ActionChains class
    - Syntax

    from selenium.webdriver.commom.action_chains import ActionChains

    action = ActionChains(driver)
    action.drag_and_drop(source, target).perform()

    ✅ Alternative Method (More Reliable)
    
    action.click_and_hold(source)\
            .move_to_element(target)
            .release()
            .perform()
        
✅ Example Code
from selenuim import webdriver
from selenium.webdriver.common.by import By
from selenium.webdriver.common.action_chains import ActionChains

driver = webdriver.Firefox()

driver.get("https://demoqa.com/droppable")

source = driver.find_element(By.ID, "draggable")
target = driver.find_element(By.ID, "droppable")

actions = ActionChains()
actions.drag_and_drop(source , target).perform()

✅ When Drag and Drop Fails?
- Common reasons
    - Element not visible
    - Element inside iframe
    - Javascript-based UI (React , Angular)
    - Timing Issues

    ✅ Solutions
    - Use Explicit wait
    - Switch to iframe

    driver.switch_to_iframe("frame_name")
    - use click_and_hold and move_to_element and release and perform
    - Use Javascript executor(advanced)

✅ Types of Drag and Drop
- 1. Element to Element
- By Offset(x, y)
    actions.drag_and_drop_by_offset(source, 100 , 50).perform()

✅ Key Points for Interview
- Use actionChains
- Works on mouse interactions
- Not always reliable -> Alternative approach needed
- Requires visible & interactable elements


